UTILITIES
•	Rural power is connected to the dwelling and main bore. 
•	Telephone – landline and mobile coverage over most of the property.

IMPROVEMENTS
Jarrega has adequate improvements 
•	The 3-bedroom home is used as a caretakers/managers accommodation with plenty of bore water to keep the gardens green and the house cool.
•	Variety of old sheds used for equipment storage and workshop.
•	Purpose built Fertiliser/Feed Shed with concrete walls and high fixed roof.
•	Excellent steel cattle yards built to handle station cattle, well engineered and fit for purpose.


WATER DEVELOPMENT POTENTIAL
Jerraga is in the Morrison subarea of the Arrowsmith groundwater area.  

Water is available for licensing from the Yarragadee and Parmelia aquifers.   The water quality of this aquifer in other areas where it occurs is usually brackish and it can supply more than 500 kL/day (kilolitres per day). It may be possible to have a licence from this aquifer, but an applicant would have to conduct their own investigations.

Currently there is 1,000,000 kilolitres available for licensing from the Yarragadee and 3,940,000 kilolitres from the Parmelia, these figures can change at any time.  The figure available for licensing does not indicate how much water could be pumped from the property, or what would be licensed.

The Yarragadee is capable of providing large supplies of up to 1000 kL/day, it’s quality can range from fresh to brackish, and there is no data about its quality in this location.  The Parmelia is capable of moderate supplies; up to 500 kL/day, and it is usually fresh to marginal. 

For further information about licensing process and general information about the Arrowsmith groundwater area, you can find the allocation plan for the area with a link to the plan here:
https://www.water.wa.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0008/1610/95132.pdf
